narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The course gives you a good survey of revolutionary European history from the French Revolution onwards. Due to the short length of YSS, the content is not delved into in depth though.

I had studied the revolutions talked aobut in this class before, but this class allowed me to consider them within a revolutionary context, interconnected to each other. I also learned a lot about revolutionary theory and common practices.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
The course was structured into two 3 hour 15 minute Zoom classes a week, where the professor started with a lecture, then discussion, then a shorter lecture on relevant media. 
While I enjoyed all the content and the professor was very knowledgeable about the content material, the long run time of the class made it pretty difficult to focus, even with a 10 minute break in between. I felt that the lecture material could also have been assigned as reading to extend the amount of time we had for discussion instead.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I recommend it to students who want a survey humanities course on European history that is not overly difficult. It may be not in depth enough for serious students of history though.
